main_7420612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ffw1719409087502.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ffw1719409087502.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ffw1719409087502.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cbm1665702776349\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n SQL and Stored Procedures Support\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__sql_and_stored_procedures_support_144505\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__p_d47492e1_d47493e1_d47494e1\">The following table shows the functionality supported by the database connector</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__li_d23708e1_d23709e1_d23710e1\">SQL Support—indicates whether you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript command and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fvo1665702607150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fvo1665702607150.html\" title=\"Pass a DML statement to the specified DBMS path.\">sql</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ivr1665702776431.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ivr1665702776431.html\" title=\"Use the SQL Editor to send ad hoc queries to the database. This is only supported by databases that include a Data Manipulation Language (DML).\">SQL Editor</a>.\n                        </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__li_d23711e1_d23712e1_d23713e1\">Stored Procedures—indicates whether the connector can generate stored procedures for the most basic I/O operations.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__li_d23714e1_d23715e1_d23716e1\">Service Stored Procedures—indicates whether the connector supports service stored procedures, which enable stored procedures to be executed using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> ProcScript statement. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wjs1665702772472.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wjs1665702772472.html\" title=\"Uniface supports the execution of DBMS stored procedures by using the activate statement to address a Stored Procedure Component defined with the Signature Editor. This concept is referred to within Uniface as Service Stored Procedures.\">Service Stored Procedures (SSPs)</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pau1665702776582.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pau1665702776582.html\" title=\"Create a signature for a service stored procedure, in which one or more stored procedures are represented to Uniface as operations.\">Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures</a>.\n                        </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"5\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">SQL and Stored Procedures Support</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Connector</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">SQL Support?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Stored Procedures?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Service Stored Procedures?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">Details</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n DB2\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"det1665702776657.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/det1665702776657.html\">SQL Support on DB2</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrh1665702776725.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrh1665702776725.html\" title=\"DB2 service stored procedures can be invoked by creating a Uniface signature and using the activate ProcScript command.\">DB2 Service Stored Procedures</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n Informix\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"paj1665702776864.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/paj1665702776864.html\" title=\"The sql ProcScript command and the SQL Editor are supported.\">SQL Support on Informix</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ewh1665702776933.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ewh1665702776933.html\" title=\"The INF connector generates stored procedures for the most basic I/O operations in Informix. A stored procedure is one or more SQL statements which have already been parsed and compiled.\">Informix Stored Procedures</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zwq1665702777008.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zwq1665702777008.html\" title=\"Uniface can execute Informix stored procedures by activating a stored procedure service, define in the Signature Editor.\">Informix Service Stored Procedures</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n LDAP\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n MS SQL Server\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oxg1665702777077.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxg1665702777077.html\" title=\"The MSS connector supports the sql ProcScript instruction. Some restrictions apply.\">SQL Support for Microsoft SQL Server</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tlk1665702777147.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlk1665702777147.html\" title=\"Whenever possible or desirable, the connector generates stored procedures for most basic I/O operations. A stored procedure encapsulates one or more SQL statements and is stored in compiled format. During execution, the parsing phase can be skipped.\">Stored Procedures on Microsoft SQL Server</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"brk1665702777359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/brk1665702777359.html\" title=\"Service stored procedures are supported for the Microsoft SQL Server connector.\">Service Stored Procedures on Microsoft SQL Server</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n MySQL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yhg1665702777428.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yhg1665702777428.html\" title=\"Both the sql ProcScript command and SQL Editor are supported.\">SQL Support on MySQL</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jep1665702777506.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jep1665702777506.html\" title=\"Service stored procedures are supported for the MySQL connector.\">MySQL Service Stored Procedures</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n ODBC\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bns1665702777767.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bns1665702777767.html\">SQL Support on ODBC</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n Oracle\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yih1665702777837.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yih1665702777837.html\" title=\"Both the sql ProcScript statement and the SQL Editor are supported.\">SQL Support on Oracle</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ygq1665702777908.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ygq1665702777908.html\" title=\"Uniface generates stored packages containing procedures for most basic I/O operations.\">Oracle Stored Packages</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n PostgreSQL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nzp1665702776275.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nzp1665702776275.html\" title=\"The PGS connector supports the sql ProcScript instruction. Some restrictions apply.\">SQL Support for PostgreSQL</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvh1665702777986.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvh1665702777986.html\" title=\"Whenever possible or desirable, the connector generates stored procedures for most basic I/O operations. A stored procedure encapsulates one or more SQL statements and is stored in compiled format. During execution, the parsing phase can be skipped.\">Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqs1665702778056.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqs1665702778056.html\" title=\"Service stored procedures are supported for the PGS connector.\">Service Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n Sequential\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n SQLite\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yar1719417567610.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yar1719417567610.html\" title=\"Both the sql ProcScriptinstruction and SQL Editor are supported.\">SQL Support on SQLite</a>.\n                             </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n Sybase\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n Yes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\">\n                              For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pzg1665702778200.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pzg1665702778200.html\" title=\"The Sybase connector fully supports the sql ProcScript command and SQL Workbench.\">SQL Support on Sybase</a>.\n                              <p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xfd1665702778269.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xfd1665702778269.html\" title=\"The SYB connector supports the use of Sybase stored procedures. These can also be activated as service stored procedures.\">Sybase Stored Procedures</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__1\">\n TXT\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__2\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__4\">\n No\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cbm1665702776349__table_d4469e1_d4470e1_d4471e1__entry__5\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fvo1665702607150.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>sql</a><p>Pass a DML statement to the specified DBMS path.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wjs1665702772472.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Service Stored Procedures (SSPs)</a><p>Uniface supports the execution of DBMS stored procedures by using the activate statement to address a Stored Procedure Component defined with the Signature Editor. This concept is referred to within Uniface as Service Stored Procedures.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pau1665702776582.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures</a><p>Create a signature for a service stored procedure, in which one or more stored procedures are represented to Uniface as operations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7420612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7420612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SQL and Stored Procedures Support Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SQL and Stored Procedures Support For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures. The following table shows the functionality supported by the database connector SQL Support—indicates whether you can use the sql ProcScript command and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. For more information, see sql and SQL Editor . Stored Procedures—indicates whether the connector can generate stored procedures for the most basic I/O operations. Service Stored Procedures—indicates whether the connector supports service stored procedures, which enable stored procedures to be executed using the activate ProcScript statement. For more information, see Service Stored Procedures (SSPs) and Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures . Table 1. SQL and Stored Procedures Support Connector SQL Support? Stored Procedures? Service Stored Procedures? Details DB2 Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support on DB2 and DB2 Service Stored Procedures . Informix Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support on Informix , Informix Stored Procedures and Informix Service Stored Procedures . LDAP No No No MS SQL Server Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support for Microsoft SQL Server , Stored Procedures on Microsoft SQL Server and Service Stored Procedures on Microsoft SQL Server . MySQL Yes No Yes For more information, see SQL Support on MySQL and MySQL Service Stored Procedures . ODBC Yes No No For more information, see SQL Support on ODBC . Oracle Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support on Oracle and Oracle Stored Packages . PostgreSQL Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support for PostgreSQL , Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL and Service Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL . Sequential No No No SQLite Yes No No For more information, see SQL Support on SQLite . Sybase Yes Yes Yes For more information, see SQL Support on Sybase . For more information, see Sybase Stored Procedures . TXT No No No Related Links sql Pass a DML statement to the specified DBMS path. Service Stored Procedures (SSPs) Uniface supports the execution of DBMS stored procedures by using the activate statement to address a Stored Procedure Component defined with the Signature Editor. This concept is referred to within Uniface as Service Stored Procedures. Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures Create a signature for a service stored procedure, in which one or more stored procedures are represented to Uniface as operations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}